g.text: Black dots show coefficient estimates from one run of a all-variables-in model fitting. Red squares show correct values.
Coefficients of variables left in the model are on average 0.01 too large (compared to real value of 0, 0.1 or 1).
Using the full model returns unbiased coefficient estimates
Simulated data with a model that explains about 33% of variation in response variable, with mild multicollinearity, by https://freerangestats.info
